TY  - JOUR
T1  - More on Confidence Intervals for Partially Identified Parameters
AU  - Stoye, Jörg
Y1  - 2009/07/01
PY  - 2009
DA  - 2009/07/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA7347
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 1299
EP  - 1315
VL  - 77
IS  - 4
KW  - Bounds
KW  - identification regions
KW  - confidence intervals
KW  - uniform convergence
KW  - superefficiency
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA7347
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - This paper extends Imbens and Manski's (2004) analysis of confidence intervals for interval identified parameters. The extension is motivated by the discovery that for their final result, Imbens and Manski implicitly assumed locally superefficient estimation of a nuisance parameter. I reanalyze the problem both with assumptions that merely weaken this superefficiency condition and with assumptions that remove it altogether. Imbens and Manski's confidence region is valid under weaker assumptions than theirs, yet superefficiency is required. I also provide a confidence interval that is valid under superefficiency, but can be adapted to the general case. A methodological contribution is to observe that the difficulty of inference comes from a preestimation problem regarding a nuisance parameter, clarifying the connection to other work on partial identification.
ER  - 

